<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="84">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="84">
- 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Machaeridia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Machaeridia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Machaeridia</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stål">Stal</normalizedToken>
contains two species, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. bilineata" pageId="47" pageNumber="84" rank="species" species="bilineata">M. bilineata</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stål">Stal</normalizedToken>
, 1873 and 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. conspersa" pageId="47" pageNumber="84" rank="species" species="conspersa">M. conspersa</taxonomicName>
I. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bolívar">Bolivar</normalizedToken>
, 1889. Both are common throughout eastern Africa.
</paragraph>
